AGI -&nbsp;"Italy and the European Union must strengthen their defensive capabilities to respond to NATO responsibilities. I repeat it here with the coherence of those who have always supported a simple principle: freedom has a price and if you make another one pay your security > you are not the one who decides fully about your destiny and there is the very possibility to fully defend their national interests." This is what Premier Giorgia Meloni says, during the premier time in the Senate, responding to the theme of European Defence.
"The time has come when NATO takes more consideration the South side of the Alliance.
"Stressing the Defense does not mean to deal with strengthening the armaments that is still fundamental," said the premier. "Italy will reach in 2025 the target of 2% of GDP" on the expenses of Defense >, guaranteed Meloni.<br> "Without defense there is no security and without security there is no freedom," says the premier, recalling how the reinforcement of Defense is "one of the points in the majority program". "To keep the commitments made is fundamental, we will do it and do it," he concludes.&nbsp;
Italy's credibility is also demonstrated by the "renewed appeal of public bonds. >It says the spread that liked so much as an evaluation element today is more than halved than when we settled and here we talk about something that is actually very concrete because &nbsp; a lower spread means billions of interest on public debt saved by the state with resources that can be intended for other needs, health, education, support for lower incomes".&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
"The parliamentary budget office - Meloni said in the premier time in the Senate > - calculated that in only two years '25-'26 this savings should amount to about 10 billion and a half euros. It is a credibility that we have built with a serious policy on public accounts, public accounts that have evidenced a better trend of expectations despite the legacy we had collected and that has allowed Italy to return to primary surplus already in 2024. We are the only nation in the G7 after Covid succeeded," he concluded.
<h2> Energy costs
&nbsp;"The objective is to reduce structurally the costs" of energy that "weigh on families as ponds".
<h2>"Maximum number of employees
"We have reached the maximum level of employment ever" and added "We want to continue on this road, our will is to take a few more steps" on the theme of employment. &nbsp;
Industry 5.0 and Transition 4.0
"We are considering whether there are margins with the European Commission to include" Industry 5.0 and Transition 4.0 in Pnrr. The President of the Council said this by answering a question of the Five Star Movement.
"I recognize the effectiveness of Industry 4.0, I am an honest person when something worked I recognize it," said the premier, while for Transition 5.0 "the results in terms of circulation are seen, but we have no problem evaluating in the coming weeks the real growth curve and possibly redesigning its use. The option already advanced to the table with the productive categories in the context of that revision of the Pnrr that we intend to start with the European Commission".
< blockquote
Death at work plagues that we can no longer tolerate
&nbsp;
</blockquote
"Today we will meet the unions and we will discuss how to spend the best" financial resources allocated for safety at work.<br> said the premier also talking about "our proposal to strengthen the system of incentives and disincentives based on their conduct on safety". The comparison with the unions will be "in the merit without any kind of prejudice". "The deaths at work are a plague that we can no longer tolerate." &nbsp;
"Employment growth, the protection of purchasing power, the increase in wages are a priority that this majority and this government have clear from their settlement, priority which we consider indispensable, fundamental both from the social point of view and from the macroeconomic point of view."
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
<h2>"Next with Albania protocol"</h2>
"We are going ahead on the Albania protocol. At the end of this week more than 25% of the migrants "held in Albania will already be repatriated. The procedures are very fast, we want an Italy able to enforce the rules." So premier Giorgia Meloni at the premier time in the Senate on immigration.
<h2> On the reforms "advanced"
Reforms? "The premier is going on, I will continue to consider it the mother of all reforms. It depends on Parliament, but the majority are willing to proceed in a sent manner, as on the reform of Justice." He said.&nbsp;
<h2> Automotive industry crushed by ideologies</h2>
"I imagine that we know that the decline of industrial production is not an Italian dynamic, but a problem characterized by the main European economies and on the contrary, in a general context of production contraction, for paradox, Italy makes record one of the best performances: the industrial production index fell by 2.4% compared to the pre-Covid period, Germany to -8.9%, France -3.4%". &nbsp;<br> "Negative conjunction is largely linked to the automotive sector, which has been crushed by ideological madness and an ecological transition incompatible with the sustainability of productive systems - it has observed -. Despite this scenario Italy last year exported goods for a value of 623 billion euros, with a diversification of the production system that places us among the first in the G20".
